The other main activity was to engage in Partnership's with other firms in Zimbabwe. The main purpose for the partnership was to share developer resources and develop strategic sales partnerships in a mutually beneficial way. Furthermore, ensuring that the client's needs are met was part of the activities. 

Other activities included attending meetings to network with the clients and it was through Zoom and Google meeting since the geographical places were different. Since most of work was being held online the other part as to analyze data and metrics it tracks the progress of the work. It was done through emailing to the authorities in charge of the information. The other key role was to report the progress to my mentors so that they will prove the meetings or partnerships deals with the Upper management s deals with the Upper management. 

 

Challenges faced   

One of the most challenging aspects of this project was ensuring that the network coverage with the lead personnel was adequate. A lot of the information on the companies' websites was not up-to-date and there was a lot of outdated information. As well as that, a personal research outreach was carried out by contacting companies of interest, but only a small number responded. It has been found that using multiple communication channels such as email and phone calls was not sufficient because some of the emails would end up in a spam folder. The result of this would be that they would never be seen by anyone. 

While I was able to get the leads' contact information, the key challenge was finding a time that worked for both parties. A Zimbabwean is 3 hours and 30 minutes behind an Indian in terms of their time zone. In fact, the time would be fixed since any circumstances that may change may result in a change in time due to different working conditions. This meant that I needed to find a common time window that would work for both parties despite the considerable time difference. I had to consider the different working hours, time zones, and other commitments that the leads had when scheduling the meetings. Because of the unavailability of Wi-Fi connectivity, the meetings would not be completed and would be adjourned for another day. This would delay the work on projects. 

Problem Handling  

Due to the time difference between continents, the following methods were used to solve the problems: 

  

Organizing a meeting and updating Google Calendar for the host and clients.  

 

Checking with clients the day before to ensure they will be available.  

  

A few minutes before the meeting, I will remind those in attendance.

Learning Outcomes 

Some important learning objectives for a junior business development executive include 

  

Developing effective communication and networking abilities to properly engage potential clients 

  

Developing a thorough grasp of the company's offerings to successfully pitch and sell to clients 

  

Learning how to find and qualify leads, as well as handle the sales process efficiently. 

  

Strengthening negotiating and persuasive abilities to complete agreements and meet sales goals. 

  

Developing solid client connections and recognizing their demand for exceptional customer service.  

 

Data analysis
